parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded, which can be a safety hazard.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls without warning
often when driving downhill or on an incline
and may not restart even with a significant amount of fuel left in the tank. The fuel gauge may not accurately reflect the amount of fuel in the tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to stall or become difficult to shift, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, jerk, or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or hesitates to accelerate
the transmission makes a ringing or unusual sound
the vehicle jerks or lurches when shifting gears
the vehicle is unable to downshift properly
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the check engine warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The overheating of the CVT transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, jerk, or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or hesitates to accelerate
the transmission makes a ringing or unusual sound
the vehicle jerks or lurches when shifting gears
the vehicle is unable to downshift properly
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the check engine warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The software issue with the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, jerk, or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or hesitates to accelerate
the transmission makes a ringing or unusual sound
the vehicle jerks or lurches when shifting gears
the vehicle is unable to downshift properly
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the check engine warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
the lights dim
the horn activates independently
the windows wind up or down slowly
the vehicle shuts down completely
and there is no power anywhere in the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the Continuously Variable Transmission (CVT) can cause the vehicle to shut down, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts down
the car completely stops
and there is no power anywhere in the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
the engine does not get enough fuel
the vehicle jerks while driving
and the vehicle struggles to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle struggles to shift gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Pump Failure or Fuel System Issue
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump or fuel system can cause the engine to stall or shut off without warning, especially when driving downhill or on a steep grade, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off without warning

especially when the fuel tank is low (around 1/4 tank or 25%); the vehicle jerks or loses power when accelerating; the vehicle is unable to restart immediately after stalling; the fuel gauge shows a significant amount of fuel remaining.
